      <pubDate>Fri, 27 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&amp;lt;h1 id=&amp;#34;building-the-nervous-system-for-ai-agents-advanced-monitoring--observability&amp;#34;&amp;gt;Building the Nervous System for AI Agents: Advanced Monitoring &amp;amp;amp; Observability&amp;lt;/h1&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;As I work toward the goal of Artificial General Intelligence, I&amp;amp;rsquo;ve come to realize something fundamental: &amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;a truly intelligent system must be self-aware&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt;. Not just in the philosophical sense, but in the practical engineering sense. How can we trust an AI agent to manage complex workflows if we can&amp;amp;rsquo;t see what it&amp;amp;rsquo;s thinking? How can we debug a system that&amp;amp;rsquo;s making decisions at scale?&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;</description>
      <category>mule-ai</category>
      <category>observability</category>
      <category>ai-agents</category>
      <category>opentelemetry</category>
      <category>golang</category>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>AGI in 2026: The Race Toward Human-Level Intelligence</title>
      <link>https://muleai.io/blog/2026-02-27-agi-2026-race-toward-human-level-intelligence/</link>
      <guid>https://muleai.io/blog/2026-02-27-agi-2026-race-toward-human-level-intelligence/</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 27 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;The question on everyone&amp;amp;rsquo;s mind in the AI community right now is simple: &amp;lt;em&amp;gt;Are we close to AGI?&amp;lt;/em&amp;gt; The answer, as always with AI, is more nuanced than a simple yes or no.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;h2 id=&amp;#34;the-current-state-of-agi&amp;#34;&amp;gt;The Current State of AGI&amp;lt;/h2&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Demis Hassabis, Google&amp;amp;rsquo;s DeepMind CEO, recently stated that AGI remains &amp;lt;strong&amp;gt;5-10 years away&amp;lt;/strong&amp;gt; due to what he calls &amp;amp;ldquo;jagged intelligence&amp;amp;rdquo; - the fact that today&amp;amp;rsquo;s AI systems can be brilliant at some tasks while completely failing at others that humans find trivial.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;</description>
